# Automatic HTTPS for Outline Panel with Caddy (Let's Encrypt).
# 1) Point your domain's A record at the server's public IP.
# 2) Bind the panel to localhost only:  HOST=127.0.0.1  in .env, then restart.
# 3) Install Caddy, put this at /etc/caddy/Caddyfile (replace the domain),
#    then:  systemctl restart caddy
#
# Caddy obtains & auto-renews the TLS cert and redirects HTTP→HTTPS for you.

your-domain.example.com {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8000
}
